    <question>
      <text>If a, b, c are three non-zero vectors such that a x b = c and b x c = a, then:</text>
      <option id="A">|a|=|c|, |b|=1</option>
      <option id="B">|a|=|b|, |c|=1</option>

      <answer>A</answer>
      <explanation>a x b = c -&gt; a, b, c are mutually perpendicular. |a||b| sin 90 = |c| -&gt; |a||b| = |c|. Similarly |b||c| = |a|. Multiplying gives |b|^2 = 1.</explanation>
