      <option id="C">w = 0 only</option>
      
      <answer>A</answer>
      <explanation>No exchange of any kind.</explanation>
    </question>
    <question>
      <text>Minor M_11 of [[1, 2], [3, 4]] is ____.</text>
      <option id="A">4</option>
      <option id="B">1</option>
      <option id="C">2</option>
      <option id="D">3</option>
      <answer>A</answer>
      <explanation>Delete row 1 and column 1.</explanation>
    </question>
    <question>
      <text>Central metal atom/ion and ligands bound to it are enclosed in ____.</text>
      <option id="A">Coordination sphere (Square brackets)</option>
      <option id="B">Coordination polyhedron</option>

      <answer>A</answer>
      <explanation>Example: [Co(NH3)6]3+.</explanation>
    </question>
    <question>
      <text>Result of 1.2 + 3.45 with significant figures:</text>
      <option id="A">4.7</option>
      <option id="B">4.65</option>
      <option id="C">4.6</option>
      <option id="D">5</option>
      <answer>A</answer>
      <explanation>Least decimal places (1).</explanation>
    </question>
    <question>
      <text>Derivative of integral a to x of f(t) dt is:</text>
      <option id="A">f(x)</option>
      <option id="B">F(x)</option>
      <option id="C">f'(x)</option>
      
      <answer>A</answer>
      <explanation>Fundamental Theorem of Calculus Part 1.</explanation>
    </question>
    <question>
      <text>Fibonacci Sequence starts 1, 1, 2, 3, 5. Next term?</text>
      <option id="A">8</option>
      <option id="B">10</option>
      <option id="C">6</option>
      <option id="D">7</option>
      <answer>A</answer>
      <explanation>3+5=8.</explanation>
    </question>
    <question>
      <text>Chlorination of toluene in dark with FeCl3 gives ____.</text>
      <option id="A">o/p-Chlorotoluene (Ring substitution)</option>
      <option id="B">Benzyl chloride</option>

      <answer>A</answer>
      <explanation>Electrophilic substitution.</explanation>
    </question>
    <question>
      <text>Relation between AM, GM, HM:</text>
      <option id="A">AM &gt;= GM &gt;= HM</option>
      <option id="B">AM &lt; GM</option>
      <option id="C">Equal</option>
      
      <answer>A</answer>
      <explanation>Inequality.</explanation>
    </question>
    <question>
      <text>If f(x) = k, f'(x) = ?</text>
      <option id="A">0</option>
      <option id="B">k</option>
      <option id="C">1</option>
      
      <answer>A</answer>
      <explanation>Derivative of constant.</explanation>
    </question>
    <question>
      <text>Controlled chain reaction in reactor uses K (multiplication factor) = ____.</text>
      <option id="A">1</option>
      <option id="B">&gt; 1</option>

      <answer>A</answer>
      <explanation>Steady power output.</explanation>
    </question>
    <question>
      <text>Electric potential at distance r (axial) of dipole varies as ____.</text>
      <option id="A">1/r^2</option>
      <option id="B">1/r</option>

      <answer>A</answer>
      <explanation>Standard dipole approximation.</explanation>
    </question>
    <question>
      <text>Group 2 carbonates decompose on heating to give ____ and ____.</text>
      <option id="A">Metal Oxide , CO2</option>
      <option id="B">Metal Carbide, O2</option>

      <answer>A</answer>
      <explanation>MCO3 -&gt; MO + CO2.</explanation>
    </question>
    <question>
      <text>Self-induction is the property of a coil by which it opposes change in ____.</text>
      <option id="A">Current through itself</option>
      <option id="B">External magnetic field only</option>

      <answer>A</answer>
      <explanation>Back EMF is induced in the same coil.</explanation>
    </question>
    <question>
      <text>Atmospheric pressure at sea level in mm of Hg is ____.</text>
      <option id="A">760</option>
      <option id="B">1013</option>

      <answer>A</answer>
      <explanation>One standard atmosphere.</explanation>
    </question>
    <question>
      <text>Efficiency of a heat engine is defined as Ratio of Output Work to ____ Input.</text>
      <option id="A">Heat</option>
      <option id="B">Internal Energy</option>

      <answer>A</answer>
      <explanation>η = W / Q_in.</explanation>
    </question>
    <question>
      <text>The ratio of molar conductivity at conc C to limiting molar conductivity (λ/λ°) is ____.</text>
      <option id="A">Degree of dissociation (alpha)</option>
      <option id="B">Van't Hoff factor</option>

      <answer>A</answer>
      <explanation>Fundamental assumption for weak electrolytes.</explanation>
